  "text": "Fixed critical TypeScript build errors in the Rulesets parser package that were blocking development:\n\n**Completed Fixes**:\n- ✅ Resolved Marker type conflicts between `markers.ts` and `ruleset-context.ts`\n- ✅ Fixed all null/undefined safety errors for strict TypeScript compliance\n- ✅ Corrected test variable naming issues (`plugin` vs `provider`)\n- ✅ Verified `turbo build` passes without errors across all packages\n\n**Key Changes**:\n- Renamed conflicting `Marker` export to `DetailedMarker` in types/index.ts\n- Added comprehensive null checks in parser regex processing\n- Fixed variable references in core package tests\n- Enhanced input validation in branded type creation\n\n**Build Status**: All packages now build successfully with TypeScript strict mode. The parser package properly integrates with the branded types system while maintaining type safety throughout.",
